  "texts": [
    "This is usually not possible without approximations, and therefore, simple but generic model Hamiltonians such as the Hubbard model [15] or Kondo-lattice models [16][17][18] continue to play an important role.In this work, we will take the route of working with a model system, and we are specifically interested in the relaxation dynamics of electrons coupled to a magnetic subsystem.",
    "This falls into a broader class of problems, where one seeks to unravel the electronic time evolution after an optical excitation due to a coupling to bosonic degrees of freedom [19][20][21][22].",
    "The latter are usually either phonons or magnons.",
    "Several generic initial conditions have been studied: (i) the relaxation of a single charge carrier with a well-defined quasi-momentum in an empty band [21][22][23], (ii) the dynamics of a charge carrier in real-space [21,22,24], (iii) the relaxation of one or many electrons after an optical excitation modeled as a pulse [8,15,20], (iv) the specific analysis of the time evolution of an order parameter O(t) after such initial conditions, either concerning their decay as a function of time [19,[25][26][27][28] or the emergence of a non-zero O(t) due to the optical excitation [29][30][31].In our work, we start from the first setup, which we will modify as outlined below.",
    "We pursue the strategy of obtaining numerically exact results, and therefore, we restrict the discussion to the one-dimensional case."
  ],
